        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 30 at 2:45AM CDT until April 30 at 3:15AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 245 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Coahoma, or 13
miles northeast of Big Spring, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado City, Coahoma, Sand Springs, Colorado City Airport, Lake
Colorado City, Lake Colorado City State Park, Champion Creek
Reservoir, Westbrook, Vincent, Cuthbert, Buford, Dunn, and Ira.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 185 and 221.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
